that clears LDL receptors.

1045
00:44:04.680 --> 00:44:08.100
The injectable antibodies decrease its activity,

1046
00:44:08.100 --> 00:44:11.520
therefore prolonging the life of LDL receptors,

1047
00:44:11.520 --> 00:44:14.220
therefore more efficiently clearing LDL.

1048
00:44:14.220 --> 00:44:16.050
There's also inclisiran

1049
00:44:16.050 --> 00:44:19.380
which is a small interfering RNA molecule

1050
00:44:19.380 --> 00:44:23.760
that basically inhibits PCSK9 formation.

1051
00:44:23.760 --> 00:44:26.613
So PCSK9 focus just a different mechanism.

1052
00:44:27.600 --> 00:44:30.060
The statement here, no decrease in CVD mortality

1053
00:44:30.060 --> 00:44:33.270
with PCSK9 inhibitors just changed.

1054
00:44:33.270 --> 00:44:36.540
Finally, there is actually some CV mortality outcome data

1055
00:44:36.540 --> 00:44:38.460
with this class of drugs.

1056
00:44:38.460 --> 00:44:41.670
Honestly, it's not robust, especially if you consider

1057
00:44:41.670 --> 00:44:43.740
that these drugs decrease LDL

1058
00:44:43.740 --> 00:44:46.500
by an additional 50% on top of statin.

1059
00:44:46.500 --> 00:44:50.310
One would think that the CVD mortality event reduction

1060
00:44:50.310 --> 00:44:51.750
would be equally robust.

1061
00:44:51.750 --> 00:44:54.360
It is not, but there is finally some data saying

1062
00:44:54.360 --> 00:44:57.333
that they actually do have some CVD mortality reduction.

1063
00:44:58.290 --> 00:45:02.130
Omega-3 fatty acids, the only one that despite years

1064
00:45:02.130 --> 00:45:03.600
and years of trying, the only one

1065
00:45:03.600 --> 00:45:06.630
that actually has data is icosapent ethyl,

1066
00:45:06.630 --> 00:45:08.220
brand name VASCEPA.

1067
00:45:08.220 --> 00:45:11.280
You can see the numbers there, it does reduce outcomes.

1068
00:45:11.280 --> 00:45:13.290
Keep in mind, the one study that brought this drug

1069
00:45:13.290 --> 00:45:16.170
to market has some methodological concerns

1070
00:45:16.170 --> 00:45:18.510
and there's still question about the data.

1071
00:45:18.510 --> 00:45:20.160
In general, omega-3 fatty acids,

1072
00:45:20.160 --> 00:45:21.900
useful for lowering triglycerides,

1073
00:45:21.900 --> 00:45:24.993
not spectacularly useful for lowering CVD risk.

1074
00:45:26.610 --> 00:45:28.110
Just the words that we use when we're talking

1075
00:45:28.110 --> 00:45:29.550
about statin related myopathy,

1076
00:45:29.550 --> 00:45:32.820
myalgia, myositis, and rhabdomyolysis.

1077
00:45:32.820 --> 00:45:36.180
Even with that, we still don't monitor routinely CK

1078
00:45:36.180 --> 00:45:38.370
and arbitrarily 10 times upper limit

1079
00:45:38.370 --> 00:45:40.230
of normal is where we stop a statin.

1080
00:45:40.230 --> 00:45:42.810
And with that, thank you for your kind attention.

1081
00:45:42.810 --> 00:45:44.138
We'll see you in just a bit.

1082
00:45:44.138 --> 00:45:46.163
<v Presenter>Thank you very much, Dr. Firnhaber.</v>

1083
00:45:47.220 --> 00:45:49.803
(upbeat music)

